questiontext.text: Which of the properties does this picture relate to? [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]

generalfeedback.text:
Using the area interpretation of the definite integral, the area under \(y=f(x)+g(x)\) is given by \(\displaystyle\int_a^b \left(f(x)+g(x)\right)\,dx\).

The diagram shows that this area can be broken into two parts. One is the dark shaded area above \(y=g(x)\), which is actually the same as the dark shaded area below \(y=f(x)\), since for each \(x\) the height of the dark shaded area is the same in each case (it is given by \(f(x)\).

So the area is also given by \(\displaystyle\int_a^b f(x)\,dx+\int_a^b g(x)\,dx\).

Therefore this illustrates Property 2.
